        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 3:08PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 308 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Lexington, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Winston-Salem, Lexington, Kernersville, Clemmons, Lewisville,
Walkertown, Rural Hall, Pfafftown, Belews Creek, and Arcadia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
